  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Clone Graph\n\nReturn a deep copy of a connected undirected graph. Nodes are numbered from `1`, and output is displayed as an adjacency list.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: adjacency = [[2,4],[1,3],[2,4],[1,3]]\nOutput: [[2,4],[1,3],[2,4],[1,3]]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: adjacency = [[]]\nOutput: [[]]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: adjacency = []\nOutput: []\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return values follow the method description.",
  "editorial": "Use the graph structure directly: traverse reachable states, maintain visited or distance state, and update the answer when each node or cell is settled.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def cloneGraph(self, node):\n        clones = {}\n        def clone(current):\n            if not current:\n                return None\n            if current in clones:\n                return clones[current]\n            copy = Node(current.val, [])\n            clones[current] = copy\n            copy.neighbors = [clone(neighbor) for neighbor in current.neighbors]\n            return copy\n        return clone(node)\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Model the state explicitly.",
    "Prefer linear or near-linear graph traversal when possible."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def cloneGraph(self, node):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
